  "texts": [
    "Similarly, performance generally improves as more examples are introduced, but the increase is not always strictly consistent for both BLEU and BERTScore.",
    "For larger models like Llama 2 70B, the performance gains are more significant, particularly in terms of semantic alignment as measured by BERTScore.In conclusion, both BLEU and BERTScore results demonstrate the effectiveness of fewshot prompting, with larger models showing more significant improvements when few-shot examples are introduced.",
    "The necessity of generating precise implicit knowledgeTo demonstrate the necessity of generating knowledge grounded in specific nonsensical concepts, we conducted an experiment bypassing the nonsensical concept identification stage.",
    "In this alternative approach, rather than identifying the specific nonsensical concepts and then generating implicit knowledge based on the identified concepts, the model directly generates knowledge from the input nonsensical statement.",
    "We refer to this approach as \"random knowledge\" (RK).The results in Table 4 highlight the significance of precise implicit knowledge in generating commonsense explanations."
